	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It was alot of work for Splatterhouse because the game's original mapper has CHR-ROM swapping capabilities beyond the MMC3. I had to rearrange CHR-ROM banks and duplicate banks and reprogram various CHR related bits and change tables to get the game functioning with the same result on MMC3 as the original mapper. 
<br />
<br />I haven't updated the patch on RomHacking just because it's not a priority for me. Also since it's a patch program and not an IPS it takes a bit more effort. Because of the mentioned shuffling of CHR-ROM, a simple IPS patch wasn't really appropriate. I might update just by including a tiny IPS patch in the distribution. It would be the simple thing to do. But I'm not sure if I will bother.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


